In #BreakingDawnPart2, Volturi choir chants: "Exacueret Nostri Dentes in Filia." Translation: "We will sharpen our teeth on your daughter."
The score album for #BreakingDawnPart2 has been released.  You can hear excerpts at my website http://t.co/GQ6zzN96
Just posted a web page about the score to #BreakingDawnPart2, with music samples: http://t.co/Qjn6USzk
This Saturday the #BreakingDawn soundtrack (including a track of mine) will be streamed for 24 hours at http://t.co/CxuO4MiD.
All Things Considered (on NPR) will air an interview with me at the end of the show today. It's about the music for True Grit.
It's been announced that I'm writing the music for the two "Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn" films. So I guess I am.
Just posted my web page about "True Grit": http://www.carterburwell.com/projects/True_Grit.html.
Just got word that the Motion Picture Academy won't consider True Grit for a music award because the score was based on 19th-century hymns.
NY Supreme Court bldg 100 Centre St evacuated for fire. I'm on a jury. Had to walk down 9 smoky flights of stairs.
Just finished recording the score to the film "The Blind Side", which will open Thanksgiving.
Interscope is releasing 2 soundtracks for Where The Wild Things Are: one mostly songs by Karen O and one mostly score by Carter Burwell.
Spotted the film "The Blind Side" yesterday, to be recorded in October, released Thanksgiving.
The score for the Coen Brothers' "A Serious Man" is in the can.  Film mix is next week.
Film mix for "Where The Wild Things Are" is done. Since the film doesn't open until October I don't for a moment think it's really done.
Mixing "Where The Wild Things Are".  Karen O is coming in to do vocals tomorrow, in the midst of her album Blitz.
Finished recording the score to Where The Wild Things Are.  We're mixing the first piece now.  It may be good.
